Web Security Scanner — Authors and Contributors
================================================

This file lists the people who have contributed to Web Security Scanner.
It is maintained manually; if you submit a PR and want to be listed,
add your name in the same format as part of the PR.

Copyright for contributions belongs to the individual authors listed
below, licensed under MIT (for code) or CC BY-NC 4.0 (for editorial
content) as described in LICENSE and LICENSE-CONTENT.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
PROJECT AUTHOR
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Toske-Programer <@UnlimitedEdition>
  Role: Project creator, maintainer, operator
  Contributions: Initial architecture, backend (FastAPI + checks/),
                 frontend (index.html + blog-*.html), operator
                 handbook (PRIRUCNIK.md), deployment (HF Space +
                 Vercel + Supabase), security hardening, all
                 editorial content.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
AI ASSISTANT (coding support)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Claude (Anthropic)
  Role: Pair-programming assistant via Claude Code CLI
  Contributions: Code review, refactoring suggestions, debugging help,
                 draft prose for documentation, security analysis of
                 the codebase, migration authoring support.
  Note: All AI-assisted changes are reviewed and accepted by the
        project author before commit. Copyright in AI-assisted output
        follows Anthropic's terms and the project's MIT/CC BY-NC 4.0
        licensing model.

